2022 was very challenging and incredibly amazing. Most of all it was a year of accomplishment. From building our movie sets, launching our own crowdfunding platform, hosting an official event at @sxsw hosting a film festival for all Latina filmmakers, going to NYC for my birthday and seeing Sarah Jessica Parker on Broadway, getting a private tour of the Statue of Liberty and premiering one of my films in Washington D.C. and getting a private tour the capitol. speaking at multiple events, having Gloria Estefan at our studio, completing the @lban.insta Stanford program, going to Georgia and Las Vegas and seeing my family from Venezuela, being on FORBES and so much more!!! 2023 I’m ready. Let’s do this! #latina #entrepreneur #2022

Representation in media matters. It not only informs how others see us it impacts how we see ourselves. Been working for 20 years to increase representation of Latinos in film and television and transform how we are portrayed. When a big publication comes to talk to us, I get excited that more will learn about our mission and our work. #latina #latino #hollywood #filmmaking #representationmatters

L'ATTITUDE Ventures is thrilled to welcome Fanny Grande (@fannyvgrande), Co-Founder of Avenida Productions (@avenidaproductions), to our Game Changers Community Meet-Up event during SXSW (@sxsw) 2023. Fanny is an inspiring leader and innovator, and it is a great privilege to recognize her incredible accomplishments and her tireless efforts to empower Latino content creators in entertainment.

Don't miss the chance to gain invaluable insights from Fanny at our upcoming event. REGISTER NOW (link in bio) to secure your tickets and join us for an unforgettable experience!

At @avenidaproductions We stand with the WGA & SAG-AFTRA! Avenida is a fully independent movie studio. We have no affiliation with AMPTP. 

We opened our doors 7 years ago because the Hollywood system has been unfairly profiting from creatives and their work for far too long.  We've raised millions of dollars for hundreds of projects, and helped countless creators get their projects made all independently. 
This is why we’ve always believed in taking charge of your own destiny just like WGA and SAG&AFTRA members are doing right now! 
Si se puede! #sagaftra #wga #independentfilm #filmmaking #acting #writing

Talk about perseverance! Jose Hernandez applied 12 times to the astronaut program at NASA, that’s right 12 TIMES! I got to watch an early screening of his biopic this weekend and I didn’t realize how much I needed it. Being an entrepreneur in the entertainment business is hard, harder than I could’ve ever imagined. And on top of that being a Latina entrepreneur makes it even harder to break through. But after watching his story I saw myself in him. When you have a dream that is bigger than yourself there’s no quitting and no matter how hard it gets I’m committed to making a space for Latinos in our industry. Here’s to not giving up, staying the course, and following our heart no matter how hard it gets. Thank you Jose for being a real life superhero for our community #dreamscometrue #Latinos #perseverance #astrounaut #shootforthestars

Moments of gratitude.  Grateful for my family especially my parents. Grateful for my best friend, business and life partner, my husband. Grateful for God always taking care of us and giving us the strength to keep going no matter how tough things get. Grateful for my life’s purpose that guides me. Grateful for our home. Grateful that the kids are taken care of and thriving. Grateful to live in LA. Grateful for the positive impact I get to make every day. Grateful for my community and how you trust and uplift me. Grateful for health. Grateful for this beautiful country that is once again finding its voice. Grateful for new friends and long friendships. Grateful for all the miracles that keep showing up. Grateful for health. Grateful that God uses me to make other people’s dreams come true. Grateful for our studio and what it meant for the community at large. Grateful for our new place and the platform we are building. So freaking excited about that!!!! Grateful that we all get to build it together. Grateful for growing into myself. What are you grateful for?

Long post alert 🚨 

As I type this I'm overcome with pride and so humbled by the accomplishment. We launched Support Our Story as a way to create a pipeline for creatives to get their projects funded and to serve as a sort of incubator. Last week we crossed $1 million raised. I'm so happy I want to cry. 80 projects that celebrate our talent, our communities, and our diversity, have been funded! Hundreds of creatives from across the country have been hired. Because of these funds, our clients have attended film festivals, received awards, sold their projects, screened their films at movie theaters, and made their dreams come true. But it's you! The 9200 backers that so far have contributed to these projects, who deserve all the praise. THANK YOU! And Thank you to our clients who have trusted us and followed my coaching (even when I'm tough) Here's to raising WAY MORE $$$$ and making Hollywood a more inclusive industry. #crowdfunding #hollywood #representationmatters #supportourstory

#DemandMore
Together we say ¡PÁGAME! on #LatinaEqualPay Day. Latinas are paid just 52 cents, on average, for every $1 a white man is paid, resulting in lost pay amounting to over 1 million dollars over the course of a 40 year career. We can’t wait to be paid equally, and we shouldn’t have to. We must be paid fully and fairly NOW. @mujerxsrising & @lclaa teamed up with @weallgrowlatina and @karla.and.co to create this year’s tee & benefit the National #LatinaEqualPay campaign. Take action at: actionnetwork.org/petitions/latinaequalpay

Another week, another #HerMoneyMoves Wednesday! This episode features @fannyvgrande, Co-Founder & CEO of @avenidaproductions . Join us to shine a spotlight on Latinx voices in entertainment 🎬

Fanny’s journey, from childhood dreams in Venezuela to challenging Hollywood stereotypes, is nothing short of inspiring. Now, she’s reshaping the narrative with Avenida, a powerhouse producing everything from podcasts to documentaries, all by and for Latinos, and the groundbreaking A+, a streaming platform putting creative control back where it belongs—in the hands of the community.
